== World 1 Boss: Whispy Woods ==

A large tree that serves as the first boss in many Kirby games.

=== Attack Pattern ===

{| class="wikitable"
! Attack !! Description !! Counter
|-
| Air Puff || Blows air to push Kirby || Jump over
|-
| Apples || Drops apples from branches || Inhale and spit back
|}

=== Strategy ===

* Inhale falling apples
* Spit them back at Whispy
* Stay at ground level to catch apples
* Simple pattern, easy boss

== World 2 Boss: Paint Roller ==

An artistic enemy who paints enemies into existence.

=== Attack Pattern ===

{| class="wikitable"
! Attack !! Description !! Counter
|-
| Paint Enemies || Draws creatures that attack || Inhale and spit
|-
| Skate || Moves around the arena || Avoid collision
|}

=== Strategy ===

* Wait for enemies to be painted
* Inhale them
* Spit at Paint Roller
* Copy abilities may help

== World 3 Boss: Mr. Shine & Mr. Bright ==

A duo boss - the sun and moon fight together.

=== Attack Pattern ===

{| class="wikitable"
! Attack !! Description !! Counter
|-
| Beam (Bright) || Moon fires star projectile || Jump/dodge
|-
| Fire Drop (Shine) || Sun rains fire || Move to safe spot
|-
| Tackle || Direct charge || Jump over
|-
| Eclipse || Combined attack || Run to edge
|}

=== Strategy ===

* One is in the sky, one on the ground
* Attack the grounded one
* They swap positions periodically
* Watch for eclipse attack when low HP

== World 4 Boss: Kracko ==

A recurring Kirby boss - a cloud with a single eye.

=== Attack Pattern ===

{| class="wikitable"
! Attack !! Description !! Counter
|-
| Beam || Lightning bolt || Stay to the side
|-
| Rain || Drops across arena || Run under Kracko
|-
| Waddle Doos || Spawns minions || Inhale for Beam ability
|-
| Charge || Dashes at Kirby || Jump over
|}

=== Strategy ===

* Use Beam from Waddle Doos
* Attack when Kracko descends
* Avoid staying directly below
* Spark or Laser abilities work well

== World 5 Boss: Heavy Mole ==

A giant mechanical mole that digs through the stage.

=== Attack Pattern ===

{| class="wikitable"
! Attack !! Description !! Counter
|-
| Dig || Moves through ground || Follow it
|-
| Eject Debris || Throws objects backward || Inhale and spit
|-
| Missiles || Fires projectiles || Dodge or inhale
|}

=== Strategy ===

* Autoscrolling fight
* Stay behind Heavy Mole
* Inhale debris to attack
* Keep up with the scrolling

== World 6 Boss: Meta Knight ==

A mysterious masked swordsman.

=== Pre-Fight ===

Meta Knight offers Kirby a sword - accepting gives you Sword ability.

=== Attack Pattern ===

{| class="wikitable"
! Attack !! Description !! Counter
|-
| Sword Slash || Forward strike || Block or dodge
|-
| Dive || Aerial attack || Move aside
|-
| Multi-Slash || Rapid strikes || Keep distance
|-
| Tornado || Spinning attack || Jump over
|}

=== Strategy ===

* Take the offered sword
* It's a fair duel
* Match his aggression
* Watch for tells before attacks

== World 7 Boss: King Dedede ==

The king of Dream Land - but not the true final boss.

=== Attack Pattern ===

{| class="wikitable"
! Attack !! Description !! Counter
|-
| Hammer Swing || Overhead slam || Dodge to side
|-
| Inhale || Sucks Kirby in || Escape button mash
|-
| Jump || Body slam || Run under
|-
| Super Inhale || Stronger suction || Stay far away
|}

=== Strategy ===

* Dodge hammer attacks
* Avoid being inhaled
* Attack after missed swings
* Prepare for true final boss after

== Final Boss: Nightmare ==

The true antagonist, revealed after defeating Dedede.

=== Phase 1: Nightmare Power Orb ===

{| class="wikitable"
! Attack !! Description !! Counter
|-
| Stars || Projectile pattern || Dodge between
|-
| Approach || Closes in || Keep moving
|}

=== Phase 2: Nightmare Wizard ===

{| class="wikitable"
! Attack !! Description !! Counter
|-
| Star Projectiles || Multiple shots || Weave through
|-
| Spin || Tornado form || Stay away
|-
| Cape Sweep || Wide attack || Jump over
|-
| Invulnerability || Closes cape || Wait for opening
|}

=== Strategy ===

* Star Rod is required weapon
* Only attack when cape is open
* Long fight with invulnerability phases
* Most challenging boss in the game

== Arena Mode ==

After completing the game, Boss Endurance mode unlocks:
* Fight all bosses consecutively
* Limited healing between fights
* Test of skill and endurance

